    • Method Detail

      • extractWorksheets

        void extractWorksheets(WorksheetContainer container)
                throws java.io.IOException
        Extract the worksheet data from container into a file, and (if successful) mark the container to indicate that the data have been extracted. Always succeeds if the container has no data.
        Parameters:
        container - the WorksheetContainer whose data should be extracted
        Throws:
        java.io.IOException - if the extraction cannot be performed

      • isExtracted

        boolean isExtracted(WorksheetContainer container)
        Returns:
        true if the data in container have been successfully extracted

        Add restrictions to the given query so that only worksheet containers eligible for extraction are picked up.
        Parameters:
        query - Query which selects WorksheetContainers.
